    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require all children\u2019s home staff to be trained in trauma-informed care by 2026",
        "additional_details": "Children in care can often carry trauma. We think making trauma-informed training mandatory for carers could improve stability, reduce breakdowns and keep children safe.",
        "background": "Government to introduce mandatory trauma-informed training for all residential care workers and foster carers. Children in care can experience neglect, abuse or loss. Properly trained staff could improve support, reduce placement breakdowns, and help give children the safe relationships they need.",
